We would like to be able to see all the comments of the subtasks rolled over to the parent so that we can view all the comments in a single view. Right now we need to go into each of the subtask to get the whole story.

The $issueTypes variable in the velocity context for release notes contains all the issue types, even if your issue type scheme doesn't include those issues. This is because the ReleaseNotesManager just uses ConstantsManager#getAllIssueTypeObjects

{code}private Map getTemplateVariables(Action action, Version version, User user, GenericValue project)
    {
        List issueTypes = new ArrayList();
        for (Iterator iterator = constantsManager.getAllIssueTypeObjects().iterator(); iterator.hasNext();)
        {
            ...

         }
         .....
    }
{code}

Changing the above to use the IssueTypeSchemeManager instead seems to change it to return only the valid issues for the project, but I don't know if it will break something else. 

{code}private Map getTemplateVariables(Action action, Version version, User user, GenericValue project)
    {
        List issueTypes = new ArrayList();
        for (Iterator iterator = ComponentManager.getInstance().getIssueTypeSchemeManager().getIssueTypesForProject(project).iterator(); iterator.hasNext();)
        {
            ...

         }
         ...
    }
{code}

You'd only ever notice this if you customise the release notes since by default it will strip out any issue type that doesn't have issues created.

